# InScien runs with sensible defaults out of the box — `docker compose up` needs no
# env setup. Copy this file to `.env` only if you want to override something; compose
# picks up `.env` automatically for the variables below.

# Where the backend reaches your LOCAL Ollama (OpenAI-compatible endpoint). The default
# works for Docker Desktop on macOS/Windows and Docker Engine on Linux.
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434/v1

# Narration voice — any Kokoro voice id (e.g. af_heart, af_bella, am_michael).
# KOKORO_VOICE=af_heart

# OPTIONAL cloud model. InScien is local-first; leave this unset to run fully on your local
# Ollama. To use an OpenAI (or OpenAI-compatible) model instead, set your key here — it's read
# from the environment only and never stored in the database. Then pick "OpenAI" + a model id
# in Settings. Restart the stack after changing this.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# Point at any OpenAI-compatible endpoint (Groq, OpenRouter, Together, …). Defaults to OpenAI.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# Your local Zotero data directory (the folder containing zotero.sqlite + storage/).
# InScien mounts it read-only and reads via a private snapshot, so your live library is
# never modified. Find it in Zotero → Settings → Advanced → "Data Directory Location".
# ZOTERO_HOST_DIR=/home/you/Zotero
